The paper deals with the complexity of polynomial identity testing for constant-depth formulas, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory. The paper also uses algebraic techniques to prove a new conjecture about low-support rank-concentration, which is a topic in algebraic complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with geometric and algebraic aspects of the problem, which makes cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses techniques from linear algebra and probability theory, which makes cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible sub-category as well.
